TITLE: Minnesota Lt. Gov. ripped for saying parents must ‘believe’ when kids ‘tell us who they are’
SUMMARY: Minnesota Lt. Gov. Peggy Flanagan, a Democrat, argued parents must "believe" their children when they "tell us who they are" in a now-viral clip.

TITLE: NRCC drops ‘March to the Left Madness’ bracket as NCAA tournament kicks off
SUMMARY: Fox News Digital exclusively obtained National Republican Congressional Committee's "March to the Left Madness" bracket as March Madness officially kicks off.

TITLE: Georgia bill banning transgender surgeries on minors one step closer to becoming law
SUMMARY: Georgia lawmakers have advanced a controversial bill that would ban sex-reassignment surgeries and hormone replacement therapies for gender dysphoric minors.

TITLE: ND Supreme Court upholds injunction on state's plan to outlaw most abortions
SUMMARY: The North Dakota Supreme Court on Thursday ruled that an injunction on a law banning all abortions not performed in rape, incest or life-threatening situations will remain in place.

TITLE: Biden family received more than $1M from Hunter associate after 2017 China wire: House Oversight
SUMMARY: Biden family members received more than $1 million in payments from accounts related to Hunter Biden’s business associate Rob Walker and their Chinese business ventures in 2017.

TITLE: Russia flying more armed aircraft over US bases in Syria, US CENTCOM commander says
SUMMARY: U.S. Central Command has observed a concerning rise in "unprofessional" and "unsafe" behavior from Russian aircraft pilots near U.S. bases in Syria.

TITLE: Kentucky lawmakers pass bill to make hazing a crime following student's death
SUMMARY: Kentucky lawmakers passed a bill Thursday that will create new crimes to punish those responsible for hazing resulting in death. This bill follows the death of a student.

TITLE: House oversight chair Comer says ‘6 or 7 Biden family members’ potentially involved in business schemes
SUMMARY: House Oversight Committee Chairman James Comer says he believes at least half a dozen members of President Biden's family have been involved in “various business schemes” around the world.

TITLE: Marine Corps Commandant Gen. David Berger says there's 'zero evidence' DEI training distracts from readiness
SUMMARY: U.S. Marine Corps Commandant Gen. David Berger said Thursday he has seen "zero evidence" that diversity, equity, and inclusion training programs are hurting readiness.

TITLE: Tempers flare after GOP senator calls out Biden admin for lying about Social Security claim
SUMMARY: Republicans and Democrats sparred in the Senate today over how willing President Biden is to meet with lawmakers to talk about saving Social Security.

TITLE: EcoHealth Alliance: Controversial group back in the spotlight for alleged 'double billing' of Wuhan lab work
SUMMARY: EcoHealth Alliance, a New York nonprofit, is back under a microscope following a report alleging they "double billed" two government agencies for Wuhan lab work.

TITLE: North Carolina bipartisan agreement to expand Medicaid clears state Senate
SUMMARY: The North Carolina state Senate has approved a bipartisan agreement to expand Medicaid coverage. The proposal could cover more low-income adults and build more health facilities.

TITLE: Republican-dominated North Carolina Supreme Court may revive voter ID mandate
SUMMARY: Mandating voter identification for elections in North Carolina was once struck down by Democrats, but may be revived now that Republicans hold a majority in the Supreme court.

TITLE: ISIS group in Afghanistan could conduct 'external' attack against US in 6 months, US commander says
SUMMARY: ISIS-K terrorists in Afghanistan could carry out an attack against U.S. interests and Western allies within six months "with little-to-no warning," a top U.S. commander says.

TITLE: North Carolina Democratic governor’s plan to increase spending by 20% scoffed at by Republicans
SUMMARY: Democratic Gov. Roy Cooper’s big budget increase of 20% was scoffed at by the GOP. North Carolina’s Republicans originally favored an increase of around 10%.

TITLE: Sweeping North Carolina bill that would discard gun permits, mental evaluations heads to Gov. Cooper
SUMMARY: A bill that would discard North Carolina’s longstanding requirement that gun buyers need to obtain a permit and clear a mental evaluation will head to the governor’s desk Wednesday.

TITLE: Senate Republicans introduce bill codifying right to bear arms 'outside your home'
SUMMARY: Senate Republicans are pushing to codify court rulings ensuring that Americans can both own guns individually and carry them outside their homes for self-defense.

TITLE: DeSantis forms alliance with 18 governors to combat Biden's ESG push: 'Direct threat to the American economy'
SUMMARY: Gov. Ron DeSantis is leading 18 states in combating the Biden administration's push on ESG investments, which they say could harm American retirement funds.

TITLE: Florida hotel points fingers after DeSantis moves to strip its liquor license over 'lewd' drag show
SUMMARY: The Hyatt Regency Miami blamed the city of Miami and a third party after Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis announced that it intended to revoke the hotel's liquor license over a sexually explicit Christmas-themed drag show with children present.

TITLE: Biden admin's war on household appliances will cause higher prices, dirtier clothes and dishes, experts warn
SUMMARY: The Biden administration's efforts to maximize energy efficiency of appliances through regulation could negatively impact consumers, according to experts and manufacturers.

TITLE: Democrat senator slapped with ethics complaint for using official website to push re-election campaign
SUMMARY: Sen. Jon Tester,D-Mont., is facing an ethics complaint from a government watchdog after he used his official Senate website to promote his vulnerable 2024 re-election campaign.

TITLE: Senate Republicans demand DOJ sue Chinese Communist Party over role in COVID-19 pandemic
SUMMARY: Six Republican senators led by Sen. Rick Scott, R-Fla., are demanding the Justice Department sue the Chinese Communist Party for its role in the COVID-19 pandemic.

TITLE: Chicago officials rip Lightfoot's handling of migrant crisis in tense council meeting: 'Dropped the ball'
SUMMARY: A Chicago City Council meeting became tense as multiple aldermen complained about a lack of clarity and direction in handling the ongoing illegal migrant crisis.

TITLE: Marianne Williamson 2020 campaign staffers allege abusive behavior from Democratic presidential candidate
SUMMARY: Two-time Democratic presidential candidate Marianne Williamson, who's primary challenging President Biden, denies allegations of abuse from former staffers on her 2020 campaign

TITLE: Lankford, Sinema raise concerns about security of border entry ports preparedness after migrant rush
SUMMARY: Senators James Lankford and Kyrsten Sinema sent a letter to GSA administrator Carnahan regarding their concerns about southern border entry ports' preparedness.
